AB  - This paper analytically compares macroeconomic performance under fixed and flexible exchange-rate regimes. A model is developed in which the economy is stable around full employment, but subject to periodic random shocks. From the model, conditions are derived which allow comparison (across exchange-rate regimes) of the size of the expected squared deviation from full employment income in any arbitrarily selected period. These conditions are stated in terms of the variances and elasticities of particular behavioral relations.
