VL  - 9
IS  - 2
SP  - 303
EP  - 307
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/05/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(79)90011-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199679900114
AB  - The choice of an optimal policy when the foreign supply curve is unstable has been considered separately in two earlier articles. Both authors have shown that price stabization is welfare increasing if a tariff set for noneconomic reasons is above 100 percent. The fact that both achieve the same result despite the choice of different stabilization measures is taken up in this article. It is found that price stabilization through quotas or buffer stocks will have the same effect on economic welfare despite their differing impact on the level of imports under varying supply conditions.
ER  - 

